# {{PROJECT_NAME}} -- Manual Workflow Guide

> For AI assistants that do NOT have plugin/skill access (Gemini, Codex, etc.).
> Claude Code users have these as `/slash-commands` -- this file documents the manual equivalents.

---

## /kickoff -- Session Start

**What it does:** Loads context and presents a briefing with available tasks.

### Manual Steps:

1. Read `{{STATUS_FILE_PATH}}`
2. Identify tasks assigned to you (or tasks with status `ready`)
3. Pick the highest-priority task
4. Read the task file at `{{TASK_FILES_PATH}}/{task-id}.md`
5. Read the context header at the top of the task file (lists prerequisite files)
6. Read the service hub file at `{{SERVICE_HUB_PATH}}/{service}.md` if referenced
7. Present a briefing:
   ```
   Session Briefing
   ================
   Task: {task-id} -- {task title}
   Service: {service name}
   Priority: {priority}
   Dependencies: {list any blocking tasks}
   Files to modify: {list from task context header}
   ```
8. Begin coding immediately (do NOT ask "Ready to start?")

